From: etna <etna@local>
Subject: [PATCH] inject rope_builder_default_empty_stack_dfcac8b_1

Reintroduces the bug fixed in dfcac8b19ee571a2a399e189c12b2a10663ce464
("Fix broken Default impl for RopeBuilder"):

The derived `Default` for `RopeBuilder` leaves `stack` as an empty
`SmallVec`, because that's what `SmallVec::default()` produces. The
hand-written `Self::new()` instead pushes a single empty-leaf node onto
the stack, which every append / finish path relies on. The buggy
derive makes `RopeBuilder::default().append(..)` immediately panic
inside `append_leaf_node`'s `self.stack.pop().unwrap()`, and
`RopeBuilder::default().finish()` underflow on `self.stack.len() - 1`.

---
 src/rope_builder.rs | 6 ------
 1 file changed, 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/rope_builder.rs b/src/rope_builder.rs
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/rope_builder.rs
+++ b/src/rope_builder.rs
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@ use crate::tree::{Node, NodeChildren, NodeText, MAX_BYTES, MAX_CHILDREN, MIN_BYT
 ///
 /// assert_eq!(rope, "Hello world!\nHow's it going?");
 /// ```
-#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
+#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default)]
 pub struct RopeBuilder {
     stack: SmallVec<[Arc<Node>; 4]>,
     buffer: String,
@@ -291,12 +291,6 @@ impl RopeBuilder {
     }
 }

-impl Default for RopeBuilder {
-    fn default() -> Self {
-        Self::new()
-    }
-}
-
 enum NextText<'a> {
